From 104a81396d3d580a943a14fef05f57705d15a067 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 23:24:55 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 7/9] libavcodec: unified -qpfile across
 libx264/libsvtav1/libaom (vmaf-tune)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds an -qpfile <path> AVOption on libx264, libsvtav1, and libaom-av1
that consumes the qpfile format emitted by vmaf-tune's saliency.py
(<frame_idx> <I|P|B> <qp> + per-MB-row deltas).

The new shared parser at libavcodec/qpfile_parser.{c,h} reads the file
once into a VmafTuneQpFile struct so each adapter can map it into its
native ROI / per-block QP-offset API:

  * libx264: forwards the path as qpfile=<path> via x264_param_parse,
    re-using x264's own qpfile reader (per-MB extension since r2390).
  * libsvtav1: full ROI bridge. Parses the qpfile, sets enable_roi_map,
    and attaches a per-frame ROI_MAP_EVENT priv-data node (gated on
    SVT-AV1 >= 1.6.0; older releases fall back to log-and-continue).
    Per-MB qp_offsets are downsampled to SVT-AV1's per-64x64-SB
    b64_seg_map by averaging the four MBs that overlap each SB and
    snapping to up to 8 segment QPs (uniform binning when the value
    span exceeds the segment budget). The SvtAv1RoiMapEvt + b64_seg_map
    pair lives for the entire encode session because SVT-AV1 reads
    ROI_MAP_EVENT data via shallow-copied pointers on async pipeline
    threads (resource_coordination_process.c, enc_handle.c). Retires
    the SVT-AV1 deferral noted in ADR-0312.
  * libaom-av1: full ROI bridge. Parses the qpfile, allocates an
    encoder-grid-sized segment-id map (mi grid: ALIGN_POWER_OF_TWO(dim,
    8) >> 2), and per frame in aom_encode() picks up to 8 segment QPs
    (uniform linear binning when the value span exceeds AOM_MAX_SEGMENTS),
    paints the per-mi segment map, and issues
    aom_codec_control(AOME_SET_ROI_MAP). libaom deep-copies the segment
    map and delta_q[] table on every control call (see
    av1/encoder/encoder.c::av1_set_roi_map memcpy), so a single buffer
    is reused across frames. Retires the libaom-av1 deferral noted in
    ADR-0312.

Parser is bounded (NASA POW10), uses strtol + portable fgetc-based
line reader (no POSIX getline dependency, no banned-API per CLAUDE.md
§6), clamps offsets to [-12,+12] matching
tools/vmaf-tune/src/vmaftune/saliency.py.

ADR: docs/adr/0312-ffmpeg-patches-vmaf-tune-integration.md
Research: docs/research/0084-ffmpeg-patch-vmaf-tune-integration-survey.md
